17:08.958 --> 17:15.647
At his own initiative, God through the Holy Spirit selects, decides, and freely bestows these gifts in an unmerited manner.

17:16.469 --> 17:22.397
It's often been said that saving grace is level ground because salvation through Messiah is the same for everyone.

17:23.038 --> 17:25.842
But serving grace differs among believers.

17:26.434 --> 17:37.931
The phrase saving grace on level ground means that every single person who's saved is saved through faith alone in the finished work of Jesus of Messiah, not because of any personal merit or status.

17:39.013 --> 17:52.453
Whether you're a lifelong devout religious person or whether you're a murderer, whether you're a child, a prostitute, a wealthy person or a poor widow, the ground at the foot of the cross is absolutely level.

17:53.194 --> 17:56.018
We're all the same sinners.

17:56.226 --> 18:04.481
And everyone is saved only because God's grace covers our sin completely when we believe in Christ's blood, death, and resurrection.

18:05.242 --> 18:08.387
Saving grace makes all believers equal in God's sight.

18:08.688 --> 18:10.772
There's no hierarchy and no favoritism.

18:11.152 --> 18:21.170
