18:33.036 --> 18:46.529
One believer may receive extraordinary grace to teach, another to show mercy, another to lead, and another to suffer faithfully as a martyr, to another may be given the grace of generosity and so forth.

18:47.330 --> 18:51.954
These different graces create variety and beauty in the body of Messiah.

18:52.290 --> 18:56.575
but they don't create different classes of salvation or levels of worth before God.

18:57.556 --> 19:10.030
So in short to explain, saving grace is the same for all believers, requiring our total dependence on the Savior, but serving grace is uniquely given to each believer for our particular callings and vocations.

19:10.671 --> 19:20.082
All of us stand equally, saved by the same Savior, but we don't all run the race with the same assignments or the same measure of gifted grace to fulfill our destinies.

19:20.962 --> 19:24.706
